    "created_at": "2011-12-13T14:54:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2011-12-13T14:54:16Z",
    "body": "We could in principle support \"single-word\" variant type representation (i.e., use NULL) for tags with a small number of variants, but we would have to use \"tagged pointers\" (i.e., set the low bits).  In this way we could support up to 4 nullary variants and 4 pointer variants.  I would certainly be inclined to start with `NULL` or not `NULL` (i.e., option) but I think tagged ptrs would be as general as we could get.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
