    "updated_at": "2011-12-17T04:18:22Z",
    "body": "It doesn't seem like such a weird thing to me, though I wouldn't call it a super high priority feature.  Still, I'm pretty keen on the idea of Rust giving you very good control of how data is represented in memory, and I think being able to present a null pointer as an option type can be really important for something like a big array of data where you don't want to spend an extra word per item.  Tagged pointers would just be icing on the cake.\n",
