    "created_at": "2012-02-01T23:34:35Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-02-01T23:34:35Z",
    "body": "Yes, it does make things more complex. Though, frankly, most C types probably use a null pointer for this case rather than a (uint, ptr*) pair!  Basically, enums with data don't have a very natural C representation imo.  I don't know that most `unions` are immediately preceded by a uint saying which variant of the `union` to use.  Building option<> into the language would be an \"ok\" compromise.  Worse to be sure, but is it also better?\n\nI could also imagine some attributes that specify the layout as well.\n",
