    "created_at": "2012-06-01T23:28:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-06-01T23:28:25Z",
    "body": "You don't need to build `option` into the language to do the \"nullary tags are null pointers\" optimization. Rather, the compiler can do that optimization for _any_ data type that's isomorphic to `option`. There's a bag of tricks like this -- since I didn't see this paper mentioned in comments so far:\n\nhttp://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/summary?doi=10.1.1.156.3526\n\nand also a chapter in Appel's _Compiling with Continuations_.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
